    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="368"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d368">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111A.R.–N.C./46: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Erwin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-16T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 16, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4. Your no. 3, February 13, 3 p.m. By proclamation dated October 18, 1939,<note
                        n="45" xml:id="d368fn1">Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>,
                        October 21, 1939, p. 396; 54 Stat. (pt. 2) 2668.</note> it was declared
                    unlawful for the submarines of a <pb facs="0300" n="288" xml:id="pg_288"/>
                    foreign belligerent state, including both commercial submarines and submarines
                    which are ships of war, to enter ports or territorial waters of the United
                    States, exclusive of the Canal Zone, except in case of <hi rend="italic">force
                        majeure</hi>. The proposal of the Uruguayan delegate to the Inter-American
                    Neutrality Committee is therefore one which has already been adopted by the
                    United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
